    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="897"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d897">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2311</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2518. Your 3238, December 18, 2 p. m. German Ambassador here has been granted the
                    privilege of communicating with his Foreign Office through the Department in
                    cipher concerning <hi rend="italic">Lusitania</hi>. Question of further
                    privileges will be handled with German and Austrian Embassies here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
